        <p>Statement to include on retention of research data:
        Researchers are obliged to retain research data for up to 10 years’ post-publication, however your anonymised research data may be retained indefinitely (e.g., so that researchers engage in open practice and other researchers can access their data to confirm the conclusions of published work). Researchers retain consent forms for as long as we continue to hold information about the data subject and for 10 years for published research (including Research Degree thesis).</p>

        <p>Example general consent statement:
        “I consent to take part in this study/experiment conducted by [THE RESEARCHER(S)] who intend to use my data for further research examining [BROAD DESCRIPTION COMPATIBLE WITH THE USE OF SUCH DATA WITHIN THAT LABORATORY/RESEARCH GROUP]”</p>

        <p>Example additional explicit consent statement for sensitive research:
        “I consent for [THE RESEARCHER] to collect and process data on my [INSERT SENSITIVE CATEGORY LISTED ABOVE]”</p>

        <p>For more complicated projects including research involving sensitive data (e.g., researcher records interviews on political beliefs) it may be appropriate to use a table which lists each item that requires consent (three columns with response option “Yes I do consent” and “No I do not consent”) where they initial in each box. In this example, there would be a row for consent to collect data on political beliefs, another row for consent to recording and further rows (if applicable) for (i) use of recording by other researchers, (ii) consent to use direct anonymised quotes in published materials and conferences (which may end up in the public domain e.g., if disseminated online). Then, a final general consent statement would be included separately at the end.</p>

        <p>It is now recommended to comply with GDPR/Ethical guidelines that a participant retains a second signed copy of the consent form, should they wish to contact the researcher (both consent forms and, where applicable, debrief forms will have contact details for the Data Controller).</p>


